      "citation_id": "[CITATION_5]",
      "span_text": "The use of these grafts spares the patient the morbidity of a donor-site harvest as well as can be used in conditions in which the native collagen is abnormal or deficient, such as in EhlerseDanlos syndrome.  The reconstruction of the posterior capsule results in centering of the humeral head and a robust check reign for posterior translation."
